14:14.829 --> 14:16.040
That's why she touched me.
She was scared.

14:16.064 --> 14:18.676
She didn't mean to.
Thank you.

14:18.700 --> 14:20.478
I can't believe I opened
my window shade

14:20.502 --> 14:22.346
for that social media
fake video person.

14:22.370 --> 14:24.448
How did Farhana's family
even see this?

14:24.472 --> 14:26.083
Facebook. There's an Afghan youth page

14:26.107 --> 14:27.485
that's very popular.

14:27.509 --> 14:29.453
The girl from the plane
sent it to her friend

14:29.477 --> 14:30.888
in Kabul, who posted it right away.

14:30.912 --> 14:33.724
It had 5,000 hits
before we even left the airport.

14:33.748 --> 14:35.993
This is a nightmare. Look, honor
killing is against Afghan law.

14:36.017 --> 14:37.862
We can just report
the threat to the police.

14:37.886 --> 14:39.163
That won't help.

14:39.187 --> 14:42.967
Farhana's from a very rural
village called Asadabad.

14:42.991 --> 14:46.003
I mean, it is tribal
and the hard-line Taliban,

14:46.027 --> 14:48.139
the Salafi jihadists,
they are in charge there.

14:48.163 --> 14:50.107
<font color="#80ff80">JAY:</font> All right, here's the problem.

14:50.131 --> 14:52.176
Farhana is 17 years old,
that means she's a minor,

14:52.200 --> 14:54.979
and we can't keep her
unless she asks for asylum,

14:55.003 --> 14:56.247
which apparently she's refusing to do.

14:56.271 --> 14:58.082
<font color="#80ff80">MATT:</font> She doesn't
want to go to America.

14:58.106 --> 14:59.583
She wants to be with her family.

14:59.607 --> 15:03.254
I mean, she did until they
decided to kill her. Oh, my God.

15:03.278 --> 15:05.323
<font color="#80ff80">JAY:</font> Not to pile on, but there's
another complicating factor.

15:05.347 --> 15:08.859
Farhana's uncle is the governor
of Samangan Province

15:08.883 --> 15:10.695
and a good friend

15:10.719 --> 15:12.730
of President Sharza.
That could be good, though.

15:12.754 --> 15:14.632
<font color="#80ffff">(STAMMERS)</font> Maybe the uncle
could get me in touch

15:14.656 --> 15:16.300
with Farhana's family.

15:16.324 --> 15:18.369
I could explain
the whole thing to them.

15:18.393 --> 15:20.705
We could track down, uh, uh,

15:20.729 --> 15:22.506
the chaperone from
Heart Train, Leslie,

15:22.530 --> 15:24.275
she could back up the story.

15:24.299 --> 15:25.609
I don't think they'd be receptive

15:25.633 --> 15:27.678
to hearing from you right now.
We have to try.

15:27.702 --> 15:29.880
Okay, I have, uh, seen the video.

15:29.904 --> 15:31.615
Ma'am...
No, don't worry,

15:31.639 --> 15:32.950
Matt, I know it's baloney,

15:32.974 --> 15:35.453
but I did move up
my meeting with Amina.

15:35.477 --> 15:38.389
Just think we could probably
use her perspective,

15:38.413 --> 15:40.257
and since we've already
hit a few speed bumps

15:40.281 --> 15:41.959
with the Rebuild-Renew Agreement,

15:41.983 --> 15:43.494
I'm gonna need a private meeting

15:43.518 --> 15:47.031
with President Sharza ASAP just
to avoid any negative impact

15:47.055 --> 15:48.699
that this could have
on the negotiation, okay?

15:48.723 --> 15:50.735
I'm so sorry, ma'am.

15:50.759 --> 15:52.370
No, no, don't-don't beat yourself up.

15:52.394 --> 15:54.305
There's no way that you
could have anticipated this.

15:54.329 --> 15:55.840
I should have. I know the culture.

15:55.864 --> 15:57.808
I know that there are
cameras everywhere now.

15:57.832 --> 16:00.478
I'm-I'm a representative
of the State Department.

16:00.502 --> 16:01.645
<font color="#80ff80">ELIZABETH:</font> Matt.

16:01.669 --> 16:03.314
We'll do our best to remedy this.

16:03.338 --> 16:04.849
I was just saying that I-I...
if I met with the parents,

16:04.873 --> 16:06.183
I could explain everything.

16:06.207 --> 16:07.518
Okay, I'm gonna run that by Amina,

16:07.542 --> 16:08.819
and we'll see what she thinks.

16:08.843 --> 16:11.622
Daisy, you do whatever
you can to make sure

16:11.646 --> 16:12.990
this doesn't become a bigger story.

16:13.014 --> 16:14.125
Thank you, guys.
Let's go.

16:14.149 --> 16:15.826
Come on.
Yeah.

16:15.850 --> 16:17.895
Ma'am, uh, we're already

16:17.919 --> 16:19.230
coloring way outside the lines here.

16:19.254 --> 16:21.365
I don't know how long we can keep her.

16:21.389 --> 16:24.268
Well, we're gonna keep her
until we can't.

16:24.292 --> 16:25.859
Okay?
Yes, ma'am.

16:31.199 --> 16:33.934
<font color="#80ffff">(DOORBELL RINGS)</font>

16:35.670 --> 16:36.881
Hey, look who's here.
Hey.

16:36.905 --> 16:39.550
Yeah, I went out for a walk and...

16:39.574 --> 16:41.241
I guess this is where I ended up.

16:42.777 --> 16:45.689
Elizabeth's in Afghanistan, right?

16:45.713 --> 16:47.758
Yup. You want a beer?

16:47.782 --> 16:49.794
Oh, does the Pope wear a dress?
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

16:49.818 --> 16:51.128
<font color="#80ff80">WILL:</font> <i>I wanted to apologize</i>

16:51.152 --> 16:53.364
for the other night.

16:53.388 --> 16:56.867
You guys are dealing with
the whole religion issue, huh?

16:56.891 --> 16:58.436
Yeah, I guess.

16:58.460 --> 17:00.704
Out of nowhere.

17:00.728 --> 17:03.374
I mean, I've always been open to it.

17:03.398 --> 17:07.711
Thanks. Sophie's always
been rigidly opposed.

17:07.734 --> 17:09.914
And we never

17:09.938 --> 17:12.983
talked about it much at all
until last month

17:13.007 --> 17:15.586
when I looked into sending Annie
to a private Catholic school,

17:15.609 --> 17:17.821
purely for the educational benefits,

17:17.846 --> 17:20.223
and Sophie completely freaked out.

17:20.248 --> 17:22.492
Accused me of wanting
to cloister her away

17:22.517 --> 17:24.194
with antiquated religious ideas

17:24.219 --> 17:25.829
about the role of women in society,

17:25.854 --> 17:30.367
something, something, and its
inherent poisonous patriarchy.

17:30.391 --> 17:32.703
You would've thought
I wanted to boil her in oil.

17:32.727 --> 17:33.871
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

17:33.895 --> 17:36.440
I had barely recovered
from that, and now suddenly

17:36.464 --> 17:38.843
she's fine with saying grace
at the family table.

17:38.867 --> 17:41.178
What is that about?
Yeah.

17:41.202 --> 17:42.179
<font color="#80ffff">(SIGHS)</font>

17:42.203 --> 17:44.504
No, I'm, I'm asking.
What is that about?

17:45.807 --> 17:48.819
Well, I can tell you what
it's not about... religion.

17:48.843 --> 17:51.155
Mm.
I mean, come on,

17:51.179 --> 17:52.590
is that the only thing you guys

17:52.614 --> 17:53.891
have been fighting about recently?

17:53.915 --> 17:56.927
Because the tension
in the air seemed a little

17:56.951 --> 18:01.332
thick to be just an argument
about saying grace.

18:01.356 --> 18:04.224
Yeah. We fight all the time.

18:05.326 --> 18:07.738
We always have.

18:07.762 --> 18:11.509
The thing is, the making up...

18:11.533 --> 18:13.644
used to be a lot more fun.

18:13.668 --> 18:15.346
Have you guys tried counseling?

18:15.370 --> 18:18.649
No.
Why not?

18:18.673 --> 18:21.385
Well, it just feels like
the beginning of the end.

18:21.409 --> 18:24.044
I mean, does it ever work?
Elizabeth and I have done it.

18:26.047 --> 18:29.693
<font color="#80ffff">(IMITATES EXPLOSION)</font>
The soul mate unicorn couple,

18:29.717 --> 18:30.961
themselves?
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

18:30.985 --> 18:32.663
What is it Joseph Campbell
says about marriage?

18:32.687 --> 18:34.899
It's not an adventure
or a journey or a-an affair.

18:34.923 --> 18:36.066
It's an ordeal.

18:36.090 --> 18:38.636
Then we're on the right track.

18:38.660 --> 18:42.239
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font>
Seriously, when you're stuck,

18:42.263 --> 18:44.241
a third party's perspective
can be helpful.

18:44.265 --> 18:47.044
But if they're qualified to do that,

18:47.068 --> 18:50.347
by which I mean not me
and definitely not your sister.

18:50.371 --> 18:51.715
All right.

18:51.739 --> 18:55.219
If it worked for you guys,
I guess it's worth a try.

18:55.243 --> 18:57.611
To saving the ordeal.

18:59.681 --> 19:01.225
Yes, I saw the video.

19:01.249 --> 19:03.627
Our government does everything
it can to ban social media,

19:03.651 --> 19:06.830
but we both know repression
only feeds innovation.

19:06.854 --> 19:11.569
This girl's family sends her
for a life-saving operation

19:11.593 --> 19:13.637
in the United States.
Now they want to kill her

19:13.661 --> 19:15.739
for talking to a man on the plane,

19:15.763 --> 19:18.609
in the presence of her chaperone.

19:18.633 --> 19:20.411
Even if the parents are ambivalent,

19:20.435 --> 19:22.479
they get pressure from the community.

19:22.503 --> 19:25.049
Honor killing is a
marginalized custom,

19:25.073 --> 19:27.251
mostly found in the
more rural provinces

19:27.275 --> 19:29.520
where it can't accurately be policed.

19:29.544 --> 19:31.155
Some of our research indicates

19:31.179 --> 19:33.891
there has actually been
an uptick in the practice

19:33.915 --> 19:35.593
since you helped forge the deal

19:35.617 --> 19:37.728
with President Sharza's
government and the Taliban.

19:37.752 --> 19:40.965
Well, that contradicts the information

19:40.989 --> 19:43.367
the State Department received.

19:43.391 --> 19:46.203
Honor killings are reported
to be significantly down.

19:46.227 --> 19:47.738
It was a benchmark

19:47.762 --> 19:50.441
that the Afghan government had to meet

19:50.465 --> 19:52.309
in order to qualify
for the aid package.

19:52.333 --> 19:54.078
The Rebuild-Renew Agreement.
I am aware.

19:54.102 --> 19:55.579
How do you get your information?

19:55.603 --> 19:59.717
I work with an organization that
tracks women's social issues.

19:59.741 --> 20:02.253
We have government contacts and NGOs

20:02.277 --> 20:05.122
on the ground who keep us informed.

20:05.146 --> 20:08.359
So you know that this agreement
could be monumental

20:08.383 --> 20:09.916
for both our countries.

20:14.022 --> 20:17.935
Keeping Farhana at the embassy,

20:17.959 --> 20:20.771
I'm afraid that we are putting
the deal in jeopardy.

20:20.795 --> 20:22.273
On the other hand, letting her go...

20:22.297 --> 20:24.308
Could cost her her life.

20:24.332 --> 20:26.043
Sorry to interrupt, ma'am,

20:26.067 --> 20:28.279
but President Sharza is asking
to see you immediately.

20:28.303 --> 20:30.514
<font color="#80ff80">SHARZA:</font> <i>You can't just take one</i>

20:30.538 --> 20:32.850
of my governor's nieces
and lock her up in the embassy.

20:32.874 --> 20:34.218
This will not stand, Madam Secretary.

20:34.242 --> 20:36.820
First of all, we didn't take her.

20:36.844 --> 20:40.724
Farhana Radi came to us
asking for protection

20:40.748 --> 20:42.126
from an honor killing,

20:42.150 --> 20:44.628
a practice that is outlawed
in your country.

20:44.652 --> 20:47.698
Yes. It is easy to be disgusted
by such a barbaric practice.

20:47.722 --> 20:51.035
We have made progress,
but it's a strenuous process.

20:51.059 --> 20:53.971
I'm aware of that.
But isn't, isn't this

20:53.995 --> 20:57.274
the perfect opportunity
to take a strong stand?

20:57.298 --> 21:00.277
Hardly. I'm fighting day
and night to hold together

21:00.301 --> 21:01.478
the deal you brokered

21:01.502 --> 21:04.615
having the Taliban as
part of my government.

21:04.639 --> 21:06.450
Your actions with this girl put me

21:06.474 --> 21:08.652
and my government
in a precarious position.

21:08.676 --> 21:10.087
And we are working on a solution.

21:10.111 --> 21:11.522
There is no time.

21:11.546 --> 21:13.957
The story of the U.S.
Secretary of State

21:13.981 --> 21:16.093
allowing one of her staff
to kidnap an Afghan girl

21:16.117 --> 21:17.361
and keep her in the embassy

21:17.385 --> 21:19.530
is all over the news.

21:19.554 --> 21:22.232
And until this catastrophe
is resolved,

21:22.256 --> 21:25.169
consider the entire
Rebuild-Renew Agreement on hold.

21:25.193 --> 21:29.740
Mr. President,
I urge you to reconsider.

21:29.764 --> 21:31.809
This agreement is the solution

21:31.833 --> 21:34.712
to so many problems
for both our countries.

21:34.736 --> 21:38.349
Not to mention you'd be walking
away from $10 billion

21:38.373 --> 21:40.417
in economic aid.

21:40.441 --> 21:43.387
If you don't release
the girl to her family,

21:43.411 --> 21:45.122
the Taliban will seize the moment

21:45.146 --> 21:46.990
and paint a picture
of my government as weak.

21:47.014 --> 21:50.527
Then it will be only a matter
of time before they take over.

21:50.551 --> 21:51.895
Then what will happen?

21:51.919 --> 21:54.565
We will end up once again
mired in war and terrorism,

21:54.589 --> 21:56.790
and I cannot allow that.

22:01.912 --> 22:04.438
_

22:04.768 --> 22:06.794
_

22:06.818 --> 22:07.795
Amina was right.

22:07.819 --> 22:09.163
While Afghanistan has improved

22:09.187 --> 22:11.332
its numbers in terms
of verified honor killings,

22:11.356 --> 22:13.568
the true numbers are underreported.

22:13.592 --> 22:15.002
I got in touch with some contacts

22:15.026 --> 22:18.206
on the ground there...
NGOs and medical examiners...

22:18.230 --> 22:20.875
and the truth is,
the Afghan government gathers

22:20.899 --> 22:23.244
its info from police departments
and medical examiners.

22:23.268 --> 22:25.713
And, big surprise,
these government employees

22:25.737 --> 22:27.682
aren't always pressured
to be absolutely accurate

22:27.706 --> 22:29.550
about the cause of death
for many young women.

22:29.574 --> 22:31.819
So, if you release Farhana
and she were to die

22:31.843 --> 22:33.287
at the hands of her family,

22:33.311 --> 22:35.923
there's a good chance it'll
be reported as something else.

22:35.947 --> 22:39.506
Right. Thank you, guys.

22:39.530 --> 22:41.346
Sure thing, ma'am.
Yes, ma'am.

22:44.456 --> 22:46.490
<font color="#80ffff">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

22:56.501 --> 22:57.812
Thank you both.

22:57.836 --> 23:02.606
Um... I am incredibly grateful
for the opportunity.

23:03.694 --> 23:04.794
_

23:04.980 --> 23:07.770
_

23:09.614 --> 23:11.626
<font color="#80ffff">(SPEAKS PASHTO)</font>

23:11.650 --> 23:13.594
I speak for the Afghan government

23:13.618 --> 23:16.998
as well as for my brother
when I say...

23:17.022 --> 23:18.566
this has gone far enough.

23:18.590 --> 23:21.068
My niece has to be returned

23:21.092 --> 23:22.770
to her father and family immediately.

23:22.794 --> 23:25.840
Uh, if I may say something?
Please.

23:25.864 --> 23:29.110
As you know, I was once
minister of education.

23:29.134 --> 23:30.778
I know this young man,
Matthew Mahoney,

23:30.802 --> 23:33.481
quite well from my trips
to United States

23:33.505 --> 23:36.551
and from his work here
with Secretary McCord,

23:36.575 --> 23:39.120
and I can vouch for his character,

23:39.144 --> 23:41.122
as well as the fact that Farhana came

23:41.146 --> 23:44.825
to the United States Embassy
out of fear for her life.

23:44.849 --> 23:47.361
And that is the only reason
that she was allowed to enter.

23:47.385 --> 23:49.730
She is not being kept
against her will.

23:49.754 --> 23:51.789
<font color="#80ffff">(TRANSLATING)</font>

23:52.536 --> 23:54.365
_

23:56.067 --> 23:58.866
_

23:59.898 --> 24:02.143
If you will allow Mr. Mahoney
to explain, you will see

24:02.167 --> 24:04.111
how the truth has been manipulated.

24:04.135 --> 24:05.446
There's no need.

24:05.470 --> 24:09.150
We just want to take Farhana
home to her mother,

24:09.174 --> 24:11.586
who's waited all these months
to see her.

24:11.610 --> 24:14.388
She wants to nurse
her daughter back to health.

24:14.412 --> 24:16.857
Her father is angry.

24:16.881 --> 24:19.360
Oh...

24:19.384 --> 24:22.353
But he would not hurt her.

24:23.822 --> 24:26.400
No one would.

24:26.424 --> 24:27.935
We just want to take her home.

24:27.959 --> 24:30.638
<font color="#80ff80">AMINA:</font> Yes, yes, I
understand, but please

24:30.662 --> 24:33.731
take a moment to watch and listen.

24:37.302 --> 24:40.214
Now, the reason why the
video is so confusing

24:40.238 --> 24:42.683
is because of what
the narrator is saying.

24:42.707 --> 24:44.619
The girl who is taking the video.

24:44.643 --> 24:49.090
But what she is saying
is not what is happening.

24:49.114 --> 24:51.158
The music makes it seem
romantic, but it's not.

24:51.182 --> 24:53.160
<font color="#80ff80">KACI:</font> They say it's the little
things that make love bloom,

24:53.184 --> 24:54.228
and this dude knew all...

24:54.252 --> 24:56.787
When I turn the sound down...

24:58.456 --> 25:01.836
...you can see it's
just two people talking.

25:01.860 --> 25:04.472
Three people, actually,
because Leslie, the chaperone,

25:04.496 --> 25:06.674
is just over here,

25:06.698 --> 25:08.465
out of sight.

25:13.705 --> 25:16.384
You explained it very well.
You did a good job.

25:16.408 --> 25:18.719
I think I was talking too fast.
I felt like I was rambling.

25:18.743 --> 25:21.378
I've never had to save
anyone's life before.

25:22.981 --> 25:24.992
<font color="#80ffff">(EXHALES)</font> Listen.

25:25.016 --> 25:27.228
My brother is a very emotional man,

25:27.252 --> 25:28.796
but he's calmed down now.

25:28.820 --> 25:30.865
He's convinced by your explanation

25:30.889 --> 25:32.066
that nothing bad happened.

25:32.090 --> 25:33.534
Really?
Yes.

25:33.558 --> 25:37.138
He only requests that you make
a public statement about this,

25:37.162 --> 25:40.007
much as you did here,
so that his family can

25:40.031 --> 25:41.676
defend her honor,

25:41.700 --> 25:43.611
and the community will be satisfied.

25:43.635 --> 25:44.812
That can be arranged.

25:44.836 --> 25:46.447
Matt can even record the statement,

25:46.471 --> 25:48.449
and it can be submitted
to the same Facebook page

25:48.473 --> 25:50.318
which posted the video to begin with.

25:50.342 --> 25:54.889
And the Secretary of State
must issue a statement

25:54.913 --> 25:56.157
to this effect as well.

25:56.181 --> 25:57.381
She would be happy to.

26:00.318 --> 26:02.052
This will satisfy my brother.

26:07.225 --> 26:09.370
Farhana.

26:09.394 --> 26:12.106
Great news. I spoke with your family.

26:12.130 --> 26:13.307
They understand what happened now.

26:13.331 --> 26:14.709
<font color="#80ff80">JAY:</font> This is good.

26:14.733 --> 26:16.010
You're safe to go.

26:16.034 --> 26:18.245
Your father and uncle are coming
to pick you up in an hour.

26:18.269 --> 26:20.748
They said your mom's
really excited to see you.

26:20.772 --> 26:22.817
No. That's not possible.

26:22.841 --> 26:23.818
<font color="#80ff80">MATT:</font> But it is.

26:23.842 --> 26:25.753
I was there. They believed me.

26:25.777 --> 26:27.110
Uh, it's gonna be okay.

26:32.117 --> 26:34.151
<font color="#80ffff">(WOMAN SPEAKING PASHTO)</font>

26:35.320 --> 26:37.298
That is my mother.

26:37.322 --> 26:39.567
Just now.

26:39.591 --> 26:42.670
She said, "Don't come home.

26:42.694 --> 26:44.695
They will kill you."

26:51.109 --> 26:53.993
A 17-year-old girl.
I mean, it's excruciating

26:53.994 --> 26:57.139
to see her in terror
of the people she loves.

26:57.163 --> 26:59.442
It's medieval.

26:59.466 --> 27:00.810
<font color="#80ff80">HENRY:</font> Well, not entirely.

27:00.834 --> 27:02.445
There's the Napoleonic Code,

27:02.469 --> 27:04.847
which allowed husbands to murder
their unfaithful wives.

27:04.871 --> 27:09.385
That wasn't abolished in France
until 1975.

27:09.409 --> 27:13.055
Modernization is a sluggish train.

27:13.079 --> 27:14.957
Yeah. To some cultures,
it's the enemy.

27:14.981 --> 27:17.827
They see the rest of us
as having sold our souls

27:17.851 --> 27:21.364
to technology
and wanton creature comforts.

27:21.388 --> 27:24.000
Well... I have to figure out

27:24.024 --> 27:26.202
how to bolster the faction
of this government

27:26.226 --> 27:29.038
that sees it as the key
to moving forward.

27:29.062 --> 27:31.574
Otherwise,
the Taliban is gonna take over

27:31.598 --> 27:34.644
and start exporting terrorism again

27:34.668 --> 27:36.612
with the U.S. as its main target.
<font color="#80ffff">(DOORBELL RINGS OVER PHONE)</font>

27:36.636 --> 27:38.447
Is that the doorbell?
Yeah.

27:38.471 --> 27:41.617
The belly dancers are here.
<font color="#80ffff">(ELIZABETH LAUGHS)</font>

27:41.641 --> 27:44.620
All right, thanks for talking.
I love you.

27:44.644 --> 27:46.679
Love you, too. Bye.

27:52.352 --> 27:54.530
Man, you were so right.

27:54.554 --> 27:56.232
Religion?

27:56.256 --> 27:59.235
Definitely not the problem.

27:59.259 --> 28:03.172
"He must increase,
but I must decrease."

28:03.196 --> 28:05.308
I wear the bracelet,

28:05.332 --> 28:07.310
but the lesson of humility

28:07.334 --> 28:09.178
sometimes eludes me.

28:09.202 --> 28:10.346
Tell me about it.

28:10.370 --> 28:11.614
You're talking to a fighter pilot.

28:11.638 --> 28:16.252
There were days when I thought
pretty highly of myself.

28:16.276 --> 28:18.854
Yeah. Well, when I'm working,

28:18.878 --> 28:21.924
I have to be confident and in charge.

28:21.948 --> 28:26.195
It seems I don't always
successfully tone that down

28:26.219 --> 28:27.863
when I walk in my front door.

28:27.887 --> 28:29.265
Oh, yeah.

28:29.289 --> 28:30.600
Transition between professional life

28:30.624 --> 28:35.160
and home life can be... bumpy.

28:36.162 --> 28:37.873
Yeah.
<font color="#80ffff">(LOG CRUMBLING)</font>

28:37.897 --> 28:38.874
You know,

28:38.898 --> 28:40.610
the Romans, of all people,

28:40.634 --> 28:42.845
had a pretty good recipe
for checking the ego.

28:42.869 --> 28:44.213
After military victories,

28:44.237 --> 28:46.549
they would parade generals
through the streets in chariots

28:46.573 --> 28:47.917
with a slave standing behind them,

28:47.941 --> 28:49.552
holding a golden crown
over their head,

28:49.576 --> 28:52.421
all the while whispering
into the hero's ear,

28:52.445 --> 28:55.958
"Remember, you are mortal."

28:55.982 --> 28:59.695
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font> Oh, that is good.

28:59.719 --> 29:02.688
I'll try to remember that
for my next marriage.

29:04.324 --> 29:07.103
Yeah, turns out she's not
interested in counseling.

29:07.127 --> 29:10.806
She's interested in
getting me the hell out.

29:10.830 --> 29:13.776
Oh, God, I... I'm so sorry.

29:13.800 --> 29:16.045
Well, maybe she just needs time.

29:16.069 --> 29:17.213
No.

29:17.237 --> 29:18.648
Listen, I-I get it.

29:18.672 --> 29:21.150
It's-it's the right course
of action right now.

29:21.174 --> 29:22.418
We need to...

29:22.442 --> 29:25.921
need to get Annie out
of the middle of all this.

29:25.945 --> 29:27.990
How's she doing?

29:28.014 --> 29:31.227
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font> Well, she's not happy.

29:31.251 --> 29:33.629
But she knows she'll see me every day.

29:33.653 --> 29:35.364
I'm-I'm taking her to school
in the morning.

29:35.388 --> 29:37.700
And by the time I left,

29:37.724 --> 29:40.703
Sophie and I were, were already
being nicer to each other,

29:40.727 --> 29:44.140
just knowing there was even
a temporary solution.

29:44.164 --> 29:46.676
By the way, uh, I'll only need
a place to stay tonight.

29:46.700 --> 29:49.045
I'll, I'll find a hotel tomorrow.
No.

29:49.069 --> 29:50.946
You'll stay here as long as you need to.
But...

29:50.970 --> 29:53.015
Wow. <font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

29:53.039 --> 29:55.685
Shouldn't you run that by El jefe?
I'm channeling her.

29:55.709 --> 29:58.821
Trust me,
if I let you check into a hotel,

29:58.845 --> 30:00.723
I'll be checking in right behind you.

30:00.747 --> 30:02.781
Thanks.

30:06.419 --> 30:10.900
Is there perhaps a room where
she won't be able to find me?

30:10.924 --> 30:12.902
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

30:12.926 --> 30:16.505
<font color="#80ff80">ELIZABETH:</font> President
Sharza put a clock on it.

30:16.529 --> 30:20.776
If we don't hand Farhana over
to her family by midnight,

30:20.800 --> 30:22.845
the agreement is off the table.

30:22.869 --> 30:24.413
The Taliban is flexing,

30:24.437 --> 30:26.382
and Sharza can't stand up to them.

30:26.406 --> 30:28.484
Well, he can't afford to.

30:28.508 --> 30:31.220
Public outcry will only embolden them

30:31.244 --> 30:34.623
to make a play for control
of the government.

30:34.647 --> 30:36.759
<font color="#80ffff">(PROTESTERS CHANTING)</font>

30:36.783 --> 30:40.796
Sharza says that Farhana
will be safe with her family.

30:40.820 --> 30:43.232
He has her uncle's word.

30:43.256 --> 30:46.035
What's that worth?

30:46.059 --> 30:48.437
I have no idea.

30:48.461 --> 30:51.874
With all the publicity,
there will be a lot of eyes

30:51.898 --> 30:53.642
on Farhana and the Radi family.

30:53.666 --> 30:55.778
They can't very well kill her
when everyone's watching them.

30:55.802 --> 30:59.338
No, they'd have to wait
at least a news cycle.

31:00.340 --> 31:03.319
How can I send her back to her family

31:03.343 --> 31:06.288
when her own mother says
that they want to kill her?

31:06.312 --> 31:09.492
Madam Secretary, we need to get
you and Mr. Whitman secured

31:09.516 --> 31:11.193
in the embassy's bunker immediately.
What's going on?

31:11.217 --> 31:12.862
What happened? What happened?
It's just a precaution.

31:12.886 --> 31:14.930
<font color="#80ffff">(SIGHS)</font>
Well...

31:14.954 --> 31:16.989
<font color="#80ffff">(INDISTINCT RADIO TRANSMISSION)</font>

31:18.491 --> 31:20.770
What's going on?

31:20.794 --> 31:23.272
A mortar hit
just outside the perimeter

31:23.296 --> 31:25.040
of the RSM base north of the city.

31:25.064 --> 31:27.510
Launched by Salafi jihadists.

31:27.534 --> 31:29.745
Three marines were badly injured.

31:29.769 --> 31:32.715
And it's all about the girl
you're keeping in here.

31:32.739 --> 31:34.383
We're not keeping her.

31:34.407 --> 31:37.153
We're providing temporary sanctuary.

31:37.177 --> 31:39.088
Well, that sanctuary
is not only jeopardizing

31:39.112 --> 31:41.190
our whole agreement
with the Afghan government,

31:41.214 --> 31:43.192
it's about to get more
of our troops killed.

31:43.216 --> 31:46.228
You can't save every
woman in Afghanistan.

31:46.252 --> 31:47.128
I'm not trying to save every...

31:47.152 --> 31:48.497
This girl is a victim
of her own culture.

31:48.521 --> 31:50.466
And that's not
what we're here to address.

31:50.490 --> 31:54.370
And now the Afghan government
has met all our criteria.

31:54.394 --> 31:56.739
We're steps away
from getting out of this mess,

31:56.763 --> 32:00.075
and you want to throw
it all away based on principle.

32:00.099 --> 32:02.344
We have a moral obligation to...

32:02.368 --> 32:03.579
Let me tell you.
Let me tell you something.

32:03.603 --> 32:05.181
Let me tell you what I think
this is really about.

32:05.205 --> 32:08.384
This is about you letting
your judgment become clouded

32:08.408 --> 32:11.287
over the guilt you feel
because of the concessions

32:11.311 --> 32:13.245
you made to get here.

32:15.515 --> 32:17.626
It was never a perfect deal.

32:17.650 --> 32:19.662
I said that from the beginning.

32:19.686 --> 32:22.164
But it was always a better alternative

32:22.188 --> 32:24.867
to an all-out ground
war with the Taliban.

32:24.891 --> 32:26.135
And with that better alternative,

32:26.159 --> 32:28.237
you knew there'd be collateral damage

32:28.261 --> 32:29.438
to Afghan women.

32:29.462 --> 32:32.274
So, this girl now is a symbol?

32:32.298 --> 32:34.066
A gesture, an apology for you?

32:35.368 --> 32:37.146
American service people

32:37.170 --> 32:39.738
do not deserve to die for this girl.

32:42.375 --> 32:44.553
You need to turn her
back over to her family.

32:44.577 --> 32:46.712
And let's get this agreement
back on track.

32:47.714 --> 32:49.581
We need to get our troops home.

32:55.088 --> 32:56.755
I heard about the marines.

32:59.792 --> 33:02.504
We've reached the end of
the road with Farhana.

33:02.528 --> 33:06.742
I... we can't put any more
American lives at risk.

33:06.766 --> 33:08.644
Not to mention the deal
we're here to make.

33:08.668 --> 33:10.212
I understand.

33:10.236 --> 33:11.847
No, the loss of this deal

33:11.871 --> 33:13.749
could topple the government
and put my country

33:13.773 --> 33:16.418
squarely under the thumb
of the Taliban.

33:16.442 --> 33:19.722
And then... who knows
how many will be killed?

33:19.746 --> 33:21.190
At least, if Farhana wanted asylum,

33:21.214 --> 33:23.759
no one could accuse us
of keeping her against her will.

33:23.783 --> 33:25.594
No, she still insists
she doesn't want it,

33:25.618 --> 33:27.663
this is her home.
Well, then,

33:27.687 --> 33:29.331
I can't justify this
situation any longer.

33:29.355 --> 33:31.567
I...

33:31.591 --> 33:33.235
I'm out of moves.

33:33.259 --> 33:34.970
I mean, uh, I mean, anything you got,

33:34.994 --> 33:37.139
I'm open, I...

33:37.163 --> 33:39.008
That...

33:39.032 --> 33:41.543
keeps me from sending
this girl to her death.

33:41.567 --> 33:43.402
All right.

33:45.738 --> 33:47.650
You may not like it.

33:47.674 --> 33:49.808
But you did say anything.

33:57.094 --> 34:00.285
Demonstrators in front
of the U.S. Embassy in Kabul

34:00.286 --> 34:02.497
were dispersed by local police today

34:02.521 --> 34:04.166
in the aftermath of a mortar attack.

34:04.190 --> 34:05.434
Are you serious?

34:05.458 --> 34:07.102
The mortar was apparently...

34:07.126 --> 34:09.204
An arranged marriage?
This is the, the best

34:09.228 --> 34:11.106
the United States of America can do?

34:11.130 --> 34:12.873
Well, it's the best
the United States can do

34:12.898 --> 34:14.275
in Afghanistan. Matt, the guy's older

34:14.300 --> 34:16.311
and of higher status
than Farhana's family.

34:16.335 --> 34:18.813
It's a big plus... He's 20 years older.
He's got two small children.

34:18.838 --> 34:21.983
And what? Farhana's just
supposed to be his slave now?

34:22.007 --> 34:25.219
You know? Stuck in his house,
raising his kids?

34:25.244 --> 34:27.688
She's 17 years old.
Unfortunately,

34:27.713 --> 34:30.992
Afghan law gives the age
of consent as 16 for girls.

34:31.016 --> 34:33.762
As does Alabama, Connecticut, Montana.
Yeah, the difference is,

34:33.786 --> 34:35.464
uh, girls from Alabama
won't get murdered

34:35.487 --> 34:37.431
by their families
if they refuse to get married.

34:37.456 --> 34:39.167
<font color="#80ff80">DAISY:</font> It's not so out
of the norm here.

34:39.190 --> 34:41.670
57% of girls are married
before they turn 19.

34:41.694 --> 34:43.472
You can't compare their customs
to what we know.

34:43.496 --> 34:46.231
Don't you have a daughter?!
Don't you have a daughter?!

34:49.168 --> 34:52.947
Look, 50 years ago,
my mom left Pakistan,

34:52.972 --> 34:54.616
and one of the main reasons
she chose to go

34:54.639 --> 34:58.120
was to avoid an arranged marriage.

34:58.144 --> 35:00.322
50 years ago.

35:00.346 --> 35:02.557
This is still happening.

35:02.581 --> 35:04.292
<font color="#80ffff">(SCOFFS)</font>

35:04.316 --> 35:05.694
What do you think Farhana wants?

35:05.718 --> 35:07.362
What she wants is to live, okay?
Yes.

35:07.386 --> 35:09.498
And be accepted
by her family, and I'm sorry,

35:09.522 --> 35:11.266
but this accomplishes both.
They can kill her anyway,

35:11.290 --> 35:12.567
and you know that.

35:12.591 --> 35:15.203
I mean, anything can
happen when we leave.

35:15.227 --> 35:18.240
Where's the secretary? I
want... I want to talk to her.

35:18.264 --> 35:19.608
Hey, Matt, it's over.

35:19.632 --> 35:20.909
M-Sec's in there with
President Sharza right now

35:20.933 --> 35:22.344
trying to get this deal back on track.

35:22.368 --> 35:24.880
She's telling him
that Farhana's gone back...

35:24.904 --> 35:26.803
Wait, wait, no, no.
Far-Farhana's already gone?

35:26.827 --> 35:28.040
<font color="#80ff80">DAISY:</font> She just left.

35:31.610 --> 35:33.922
Farhana. Farhana.

35:33.946 --> 35:35.757
<font color="#80ffff">(PANTING)</font>

35:35.781 --> 35:37.692
I'm sorry.

35:37.716 --> 35:39.661
I just...

35:39.685 --> 35:41.663
It is God's will.

35:41.687 --> 35:43.432
My parents say this is a good man,

35:43.456 --> 35:46.291
and... it could be a good life for me.

35:49.462 --> 35:50.739
<font color="#80ffff">(EXHALES)</font>

35:50.763 --> 35:52.007
I just wish...

35:52.031 --> 35:55.310
Farhana? Come, your
family is arriving.

35:55.334 --> 35:57.368
Goodbye, Matt Mahoney.

36:01.407 --> 36:04.108
<font color="#80ffff">(GATE BEEPS, UNLOCKS)</font> <font color="#80ffff">(SIGHS)</font>

36:31.003 --> 36:32.403
<font color="#80ffff">(WHISPERING)</font>

37:01.433 --> 37:03.468
<font color="#80ffff">(MAN MUTTERS IN PASHTO)</font>

37:15.514 --> 37:18.994
<font color="#80ff80">ELIZABETH:</font> <i>You're smiling.</i>

37:19.018 --> 37:20.862
I hope not ironically.

37:20.886 --> 37:23.965
I could genuinely use
some good news right now.

37:23.989 --> 37:25.901
The Afghan government
has agreed to shore up

37:25.925 --> 37:27.369
the Violence Against Women law

37:27.393 --> 37:29.804
and they have invited
Amina Salah to be

37:29.828 --> 37:33.174
part of an independent
watchdog group...

37:33.198 --> 37:34.809
to advise and inform them.

37:34.833 --> 37:36.834
<font color="#80ffff">(LAUGHING)</font> Oh, good.

37:39.371 --> 37:41.439
An independent watchdog group.

37:42.741 --> 37:45.754
Just to make sure no one
gets the mistaken notion

37:45.778 --> 37:47.756
that an intelligent, qualified woman

37:47.780 --> 37:49.224
is in their government. Again.

37:49.248 --> 37:51.026
Look who's being ironic.

37:51.050 --> 37:54.095
I feel like we take turns.
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

37:54.119 --> 37:56.097
♪

37:56.121 --> 37:58.156
<font color="#80ffff">(CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING)</font>

38:06.999 --> 38:09.878
We are here to announce
that with the signing

38:09.902 --> 38:14.215
of the Afghan-United States
Rebuild-Renew Agreement,

38:14.239 --> 38:17.552
the United States
will immediately begin

38:17.576 --> 38:19.177
troop withdrawal.

38:21.847 --> 38:23.224
<font color="#80ffff">(SIGHS)</font>

38:23.248 --> 38:24.492
<font color="#80ffff">(DOOR OPENS IN DISTANCE)</font>

38:24.516 --> 38:26.528
ELIZABETH <font color="#80ffff">(IN DISTANCE)</font> Anybody home?

38:26.552 --> 38:28.019
In here.

38:29.822 --> 38:31.422
<font color="#80ffff">(SINGSONGY)</font> Surprise.

38:38.731 --> 38:40.241
Henry told me.

38:40.265 --> 38:41.799
How was Afghanistan?

38:44.069 --> 38:45.914
Harrowing.

38:45.938 --> 38:48.049
Speaking of...

38:48.073 --> 38:50.251
have you looked in the mirror lately?

38:50.275 --> 38:52.020
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font> Oh, ho-ho-ho.

38:52.044 --> 38:54.155
If the name of the game
is beat up on Will,

38:54.179 --> 38:56.581
I'm way ahead of you.
I didn't mean it like that.

38:58.550 --> 39:00.651
Just worried about you.

39:01.654 --> 39:04.599
And disappointed in me.

39:04.623 --> 39:06.134
No.

39:06.158 --> 39:08.403
No?
Come on.

39:08.427 --> 39:10.071
<font color="#80ffff">(SIGHS)</font> I'm...

39:10.095 --> 39:13.208
Just... talk to me.

39:13.232 --> 39:16.978
I'm not gonna... scold.

39:17.002 --> 39:18.580
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)</font>

39:18.604 --> 39:20.949
What the hell did I know

39:20.973 --> 39:23.652
about how to be married?

39:23.676 --> 39:26.655
I was 13 when my role models died.

39:26.679 --> 39:29.257
It-it just...

39:29.281 --> 39:30.992
it just looked like

39:31.016 --> 39:33.395
you find someone
who doesn't drive you crazy,

39:33.419 --> 39:35.430
and then you have dinner,

39:35.454 --> 39:39.334
talk about work, watch TV.

39:39.358 --> 39:42.137
Or you-you play Scrabble.

39:42.161 --> 39:44.929
Sometimes go on vacations. They...

39:45.931 --> 39:49.010
...they made it look easy,

39:49.034 --> 39:51.212
I guess, and...

39:51.236 --> 39:54.616
the minute my marriage wasn't easy,

39:54.640 --> 39:58.119
I-I thought
I was doing it wrong, or...

39:58.143 --> 40:00.488
she was.

40:00.512 --> 40:03.014
They fought plenty.

40:04.016 --> 40:05.427
Uh-huh.
Sure.

40:05.451 --> 40:06.661
Come on.

40:06.685 --> 40:09.531
Mm, nothing serious.

40:09.555 --> 40:12.467
Who forgot to get the bread.

40:12.491 --> 40:15.203
Who left the lights on.

40:15.227 --> 40:18.406
<font color="#80ffff">(LAUGHS)</font> Why are your
parents visiting again?

40:18.430 --> 40:20.731
Will.

40:22.601 --> 40:25.947
You were younger, so you
idealized them more.

40:25.971 --> 40:28.383
Or paid less attention.

40:28.407 --> 40:30.719
Well, you figured it out.

40:30.743 --> 40:31.886
Somehow.

40:31.910 --> 40:33.354
Henry and I

40:33.378 --> 40:35.356
often joke that we were fixed up

40:35.380 --> 40:38.293
by a couple of romantic idiots
in their 20s.

40:38.317 --> 40:40.061
Happened to work.

40:40.085 --> 40:41.963
That's because you work at it.

40:41.987 --> 40:43.198
That, too.

40:43.222 --> 40:44.866
Yeah.
Yeah.

40:44.890 --> 40:46.490
<font color="#80ffff">(TAKES DEEP BREATH)</font>

40:48.560 --> 40:50.105
I don't know, Will.

40:50.129 --> 40:51.573
Marriage is...

40:51.597 --> 40:54.075
a mystery.

40:54.099 --> 40:55.376
And a miracle...

40:55.400 --> 40:56.878
And an ordeal.
That is

40:56.902 --> 40:59.748
exactly what Henry says.
Right.

40:59.772 --> 41:02.974
You guys <i>did</i> do some bonding.
We did, yeah.

41:03.976 --> 41:06.510
Listen, I'm sorry if I...

41:08.247 --> 41:10.225
...parent you.

41:10.249 --> 41:12.761
It's not my job anymore,

41:12.785 --> 41:15.152
and I'm gonna let it go.

41:16.155 --> 41:17.599
Thank you.

41:17.623 --> 41:19.467
You're welcome.

41:19.491 --> 41:20.869
<font color="#80ffff">(SIGHS)</font>

41:20.893 --> 41:22.370
So, where is everybody?

41:22.394 --> 41:23.838
They all went to dinner.

41:23.862 --> 41:25.540
They said they'd bring you back

41:25.564 --> 41:27.108
some lasagna from Mark's.

41:27.132 --> 41:28.176
<font color="#80ffff">(SIGHS)</font>

41:28.200 --> 41:29.944
What are you getting?

41:29.968 --> 41:32.113
Um...

41:32.137 --> 41:34.372
I'm not hungry.

41:35.874 --> 41:37.318
I can't. I can't take it.

41:37.342 --> 41:39.888
I can't just stand here
and watch you waste away.

41:39.912 --> 41:41.756
I'm gonna make eggs. You like eggs.

41:41.780 --> 41:43.458
<font color="#80ffff">(CHUCKLES)</font> You... you're doing it.

41:43.482 --> 41:46.361
With cheese, right? Oh. No, please.

41:46.385 --> 41:48.730
At-at least let me.

41:48.754 --> 41:50.832
Here, you... you shouldn't cook.

41:50.856 --> 41:52.300
<font color="#80ffff">(LAUGHS)</font> Oh.

41:52.324 --> 41:53.601
Fine, you can help.

41:53.625 --> 41:55.737
Just don't get any shell in there.

41:55.761 --> 41:57.305
And that is not parental.

41:57.329 --> 41:59.574
It's just advice.

41:59.598 --> 42:02.033
Okay, I'm gonna back off now.

42:06.471 --> 42:08.449
Just happy to have you here.

42:08.473 --> 42:11.676
You can stay with us
as long as you need to.

42:14.446 --> 42:15.980
Thanks.

42:20.419 --> 42:22.024
So, like, how long are we talking?
Just...

42:22.048 --> 42:23.298
Shouldn't be more than a decade.

42:23.322 --> 42:25.166
<font color="#80ffff">(LAUGHS)</font> Stop.
Huh?

42:25.190 --> 42:27.168
Maybe just a few years.

42:27.192 --> 42:28.837
You've got so much room.

42:28.861 --> 42:30.461
I was thinking Sunday.

